      "content": "# Servo\n\nControlling servos in XOD is just as easy as controlling LEDs. There is a special node called `servo`. You can find it in `xod/common-hardware`.\n\nThe `servo` node accepts a number in the range from 0.0 to 1.0 and maps it to 0...180 degrees.\n\nLet's link `pot` with `servo` to control servo angle with a potentiometer.\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. Connect a servo to the Arduino as shown on the [scheme](https://xod.io/docs/tutorial/11-servo/?utm_source=ide&utm_medium=ide_comment&utm_campaign=tutorial_11).\n\n2. Link the `VAL` pin of the `pot` node to the `VAL` pin of the `servo` node.\n\n3. Upload the patch to the Arduino.\n\nTurn the potentiometer knob, and watch the servo turn.\n",
